book.author: Emily Brontë
book.title: Wuthering Heights (Collins Classics)
book.description: Wuthering Heights (Collins Classics) is a edition of Emily Brontë's classic gothic novel. The story unfolds on the windswept Yorkshire moors, where Lockwood, seeking shelter, stumbles upon Wuthering Heights, the brooding residence of his new landlord, Heathcliff.

book.author: Drew Daywalt
book.title: THE DAYS THE CRAYONS QUIT
book.description: The Day the Crayons Quit is a children's book by Drew Daywalt and Oliver Jeffers. It tells the story of Duncan, a young boy who opens his crayon box one day to find, instead of his crayons, a stack of letters.

book.author: Bernard Cornwell
book.title: War Lord: Book 13 (The Last Kingdom Series)
book.description: War Lord, by Bernard Cornwell, is the thirteenth and final book in the popular historical fiction series, The Last Kingdom. It serves as the epic conclusion to the saga of Uhtred, a warrior caught in the throes of shaping a unified England during the ninth and tenth centuries.

book.author: David Walliams
book.title: Code Name Bananas: The hilarious and epic new children's book from multi-million bestselling author David Walliams
book.description: Code Name Bananas, published in 2020, is a children's adventure story by the multi-million bestselling author David Walliams, known for his funny and action-packed books.
